All Classes and Interfaces

Classes
Class
Description
App
The App class is the main class of the Payroll application.
CalendarGrid
A custom GridPane class that displays the days of the month in a calendar format.
Pay
The Pay class represents a payment made to an employee.
PayGrid
A custom GridPane used for displaying pay information.
PayWindow
A window that displays the total pay for a given range of dates, based on a list of work shifts, and the tax percentage.
Settings
The Settings class represents the configuration settings for an employee's wages and bonuses.
SettingsWindow
The SettingsWindow class creates a modal window for changing the settings of the pay calculations.
ShiftEditingWindow
The ShiftEditingWindow class represents a graphical window for editing work shifts.
TimeOfDayBonus
A class representing a bonus given during a specific time of day.
WorkHours
The WorkHours class represents the number of hours worked by an employee, broken down into different categories such as normal hours, evening hours, and overtime hours.
WorkShift
The WorkShift class represents a work shift with a start time, end time, settings, work hours, and pay.
